.TH "batadv_v_ogm_forward" 9 "batadv_v_ogm_forward" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_v_ogm_forward \- check conditions and forward an OGM to the given outgoing interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" batadv_v_ogm_forward
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "const struct batadv_ogm2_packet *ogm_received "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_orig_node *orig_node "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_neigh_node *neigh_node "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *if_incoming "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_hard_iface *if_outgoing "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "ogm_received" 12
previously received OGM to be forwarded
.IP "orig_node" 12
the originator which has been updated
.IP "neigh_node" 12
the neigh_node through with the OGM has been received
.IP "if_incoming" 12
the interface on which this OGM was received on
.IP "if_outgoing" 12
the interface to which the OGM has to be forwarded to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Forward an OGM to an interface after having altered the throughput metric and
the TTL value contained in it. The original OGM isn't modified.
